In a message dated 4/10/2002 5:53:46 PM Pacific Daylight Time, 
djohnson1(-at-)snet.net writes:
> Q: Do I maybe have an odd wheel that requires a different seal, and if so, 
> how do I find out what I've Got? 

Hi Don,
You could have a 1968-71 bus drum which needs a special seal to adapt it to 
the earlier spindle or you drum had been damaged or aftermarket junk that was 
machined improperly.  Measure with a 6" calipher and check with your local VW 
FLAPS to see which it is.   Eric&Barb

